#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-05-19-mockoon-https-stub-windows.rst:9
msgid "REST APIのStubを手早い立上げにMockoonを使った記録"
msgstr "Record of using Mockoon to quickly launch REST API Stub"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-05-19-mockoon-https-stub-windows.rst:11
msgid ""
"REST "
"APIの本実装が遅れてたり、昔作ったスタブが動かなくなっていたり、ともかく急ぎで、フロントエンド開発や結合テストを行う必要性に迫られるケースという局面に最近よく遭遇します。"
" とにかく「今すぐ」「最低限のStubが必要」という状況でMockoonが便利そうなので導入手順をまとめました。"
msgstr ""
"Recently, I often come across situations where the actual implementation of "
"a REST API has been delayed, or a stub I created a long time ago no longer "
"works, or I am in a hurry to perform front-end development and integration "
"testing. In any case, Mockoon seems useful in situations where you need a "
"minimum of Stub right now, so I have summarized the installation steps."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-05-19-mockoon-https-stub-windows.rst:20
msgid "背景と目的"
msgstr "Background and purpose"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-05-19-mockoon-https-stub-windows.rst:22
msgid "REST実装が別チーム実装、開発遅れや提供サーバの不具合でREST APIが利用できない"
msgstr ""
"REST implementation is implemented by a different team, REST API is not "
"available due to development delays or problems with the provided server."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-05-19-mockoon-https-stub-windows.rst:23
msgid "早急にHTTPS通信でレスポンスを返すStubが必要"
msgstr ""
"I urgently need a Stub that returns a response via HTTPS communication."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-05-19-mockoon-https-stub-windows.rst:24
msgid "本番APIのURLに差し替えるだけで移行できる構成にしたい"
msgstr ""
"I want to have a configuration that can be migrated by simply replacing it "
"with the URL of the production API."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-05-19-mockoon-https-stub-windows.rst:25
msgid "共同開発者はPythonに不慣れなため、ノーコード・GUIツールが望ましい"
msgstr ""
"Since the co-developers are not familiar with Python, a no-code/GUI tool is "
"preferable."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-05-19-mockoon-https-stub-windows.rst:26
msgid "Dockerは利用不可（社内制限あり）"
msgstr "Docker cannot be used (internal restrictions apply)"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-05-19-mockoon-https-stub-windows.rst:28
msgid "この条件をすべて満たす手段として、**Mockoon** を採用しました。"
msgstr "We adopted **Mockoon** as a means to meet all of these conditions."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-05-19-mockoon-https-stub-windows.rst:31
msgid "Mockoonとは"
msgstr "What is Mockoon?"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-05-19-mockoon-https-stub-windows.rst:33
msgid ""
"`Mockoon <https://mockoon.com/>`_ は、GUIベースでREST APIのStubを定義できる無料のツールです。"
msgstr ""
"`Mockoon <https://mockoon.com/>`_ is a free tool that allows you to define a"
" REST API Stub based on a GUI."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-05-19-mockoon-https-stub-windows.rst:35
msgid "特徴："
msgstr "Features:"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-05-19-mockoon-https-stub-windows.rst:37
msgid "ノーコードでGET/POSTなどのRESTエンドポイントを作成可能"
msgstr "You can create REST endpoints such as GET/POST with no code."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-05-19-mockoon-https-stub-windows.rst:38
msgid "GUIでの操作が直感的"
msgstr "Intuitive GUI operation"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-05-19-mockoon-https-stub-windows.rst:39
msgid "HTTPS対応（自己署名証明書の自動生成）"
msgstr "HTTPS compatible (automatic generation of self-signed certificate)"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-05-19-mockoon-https-stub-windows.rst:40
msgid "レスポンスの遅延、ヘッダー、条件分岐なども柔軟に設定可能"
msgstr ""
"Response delays, headers, conditional branching, etc. can be flexibly set."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-05-19-mockoon-https-stub-windows.rst:41
msgid "設定はJSONファイルでエクスポートでき、CLIやチーム内共有にも対応"
msgstr ""
"Settings can be exported as a JSON file and can be shared via CLI or within "
"the team."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-05-19-mockoon-https-stub-windows.rst:42
msgid "ライセンスはMITなのでテスト利用にも適している"
msgstr "The license is MIT, so it is suitable for test use."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-05-19-mockoon-https-stub-windows.rst:45
msgid "導入ステップ（Windows環境）"
msgstr "Installation steps (Windows environment)"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-05-19-mockoon-https-stub-windows.rst:47
msgid ""
"Windowsの場合Microfost Storeからインストール可能です。他のOSは `公式サイト "
"<https://mockoon.com/download>`_ を参照してください。"
msgstr ""
"For Windows, it can be installed from Microfost Store. For other OS, please "
"refer to the `official website <https://mockoon.com/download>`_."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-05-19-mockoon-https-stub-windows.rst:49
msgid ""
"Mockoonを起動し、「New environment」でStub環境を作成 - "
"保存のためのexploreが開くので該当環境を保存するファイル名を指定＝新環境が作成されます - ポートを 任意の番号へ "
"変更（任意）※デフォルトは3001 - 必要に応じて「Enable HTTPS」を有効化 - 必要に応じて「Enable CORS」もONにする"
msgstr ""
"Start Mockoon and create a stub environment from \"New environment\". When "
"the file explorer opens, choose a file name for saving that environment. "
"Then change the port if needed; the default is 3001. Enable \"Enable HTTPS\""
" and \"Enable CORS\" as necessary."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-05-19-mockoon-https-stub-windows.rst:55
msgid ""
"`+ Add route` で以下のようなStubエンドポイントを作成 - "
"crudでGET/POST/PUT/DELETEの操作が自動で作成するのは新規APIの調整で便利そうですが、 "
"ここではGET/POSTなどで取り急ぎ立上げたいので「Http Route」を選択 - /api/test-resource などのエンドポイントを指定"
" - メソッドはGET/POST/PUT/DELETE を選択可能 - "
"レスポンスは固定のJSONを指定できるのでRESTチームと整合したJSONサンプルを指定"
msgstr ""
"Create a Stub endpoint like the one below with `+ Add route` - Automatically"
" creating GET/POST/PUT/DELETE operations with crud seems useful when "
"adjusting a new API, but here we want to start up quickly with GET/POST, "
"etc., so select \"Http Route\" - Specify an endpoint such as /api/test-"
"resource - GET/POST/PUT/DELETE can be selected as the method - You can "
"specify a fixed JSON for the response, so specify a JSON sample that is "
"consistent with the REST team."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-05-19-mockoon-https-stub-windows.rst:61
msgid "サーバーを「Start」で起動し、HTTPでアクセス確認 例： ::"
msgstr "Start the server with \"Start\" and check access with HTTP Example: ::"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-05-19-mockoon-https-stub-windows.rst:69
msgid "所感"
msgstr "Impressions"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-05-19-mockoon-https-stub-windows.rst:71
msgid ""
"flackやFastapiも選択肢として考えましたが、手早く立ち上げるには前提知識やセッティングの手間から考えて、 "
"もう少し便利なものがないかと探していたところ、Mockoonに辿り着きました。 "
"想像以上に便利で手早く立ち上げられるので非常に助かりました。同様のニーズがる方には是非お勧めしたいです。"
msgstr ""
"I thought about flack and Fastapi as options, but I was looking for "
"something a little more convenient in terms of prerequisite knowledge and "
"setting up to get started quickly, and I ended up finding Mockoon. It was a "
"great help as it was more convenient and quicker to start up than I "
"expected. I would definitely recommend it to anyone with similar needs."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-05-19-mockoon-https-stub-windows.rst:75
msgid "MITライセンスということなで実プロジェクトでの利用のハードルも低いのも魅力です。Mockoonの開発者の方に感謝です。"
msgstr ""
"It is also attractive because it is licensed under the MIT license, so the "
"hurdles for using it in actual projects are low. Thank you to the developers"
" of Mockoon."

